CORTEX MCP SERVER CONFIGURATION
================================

This directory contains the MCP (Model Context Protocol) server configuration
for Cortex - the cognitive system with 172 tools across 20 categories.

SETUP
-----
The MCP server is already configured in mcp_config.json and ready to use.

AVAILABLE TOOLS
---------------
Cortex provides 172 tools in 20 categories:
- Workspace Management (8 tools)
- Virtual Filesystem (12 tools)
- Code Navigation (10 tools)
- Code Manipulation (15 tools)
- Semantic Search (8 tools)
- Dependency Analysis (10 tools)
- Code Quality (8 tools)
- Version Control (10 tools)
- Cognitive Memory (12 tools)
- Multi-Agent Coordination (10 tools)
- Materialization (8 tools)
- Testing & Validation (10 tools)
- Documentation (8 tools)
- Build & Execution (8 tools)
- Monitoring & Analytics (10 tools)
- Security Analysis (4 tools)
- Type Analysis (4 tools)
- AI-Assisted Development (6 tools)
- Advanced Testing (6 tools)
- Architecture Analysis (5 tools)

USAGE
-----
The MCP server will be automatically available in Claude Code.
Use tools with the mcp__cortex__ prefix.

TESTING
-------
To manually test the MCP server:
  echo '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"method":"initialize","params":{"protocolVersion":"0.1.0","capabilities":{},"clientInfo":{"name":"test","version":"1.0"}}}' | ./dist/cortex mcp stdio

To see all available tools:
  ./dist/cortex mcp info --detailed

CONFIGURATION
-------------
Config file: .claude/mcp_config.json
Binary: /Users/taaliman/projects/luxquant/ry-ht/ryht/dist/cortex
Database: /Users/taaliman/.ryht/cortex/cortex.db
